Package: crazyforest
Type: Package
Title: Random Forests with Stochastic Splitting and Voting
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-01-15
Authors@R: c(
    person("Javier", "Pérez-Rodríguez", email = "javier.perez@uco.es", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Nicolás", "García-Pedrajas", role = "ctb")
    )
Description: A fast implementation of Crazy Forests, a stochastic variant of 
    Random Forests particularly suited for high-dimensional data. Introduces 
    experimental research features such as chaos-based splitting rules and 
    probabilistic roulette voting mechanisms. Ensembles of classification, 
    regression, survival, and probability prediction trees are supported. 
    Efficiently handles large datasets, including direct support for sparse 
    matrices of class 'dgCMatrix' (from the 'Matrix' package). Optimized for 
    methodological research and high-performance computing via C++.
License: GPL-3
Imports: Rcpp (>= 0.11.2), Matrix
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppEigen
Depends: R (>= 3.1)
Suggests: 
    survival,
    testthat
